// bisect: JIT SIGSEGV + over-fire (interp settles at 6; jit crashed, then
// busy-spun) when a SCALAR array::fold result flows directly into a connect.
// Found while auditing HOF STALE propagation (Tier 3.1, 2026-06-30).
// root_cause (two bugs, one repro):
//   1. FoldImpl::emit_clif wrapped its SCALAR accumulator result with
//      `array_result` — an ARRAY disc over a scalar payload. On the
//      kernel-return path the disc tag is ignored, but a connect's
//      `set_var` reconstructs a Value from the disc → interpreted the
//      scalar `6` as a `*ValArray` → SIGSEGV at init. Fixed by
//      `emit::scalar_result` (the prim's natural disc).
//   2. The fold result didn't inherit the source array's STALE, so over a
//      CONSTANT array it stayed fresh forever → the self-connect re-fired
//      every cycle (busy-spin) while the node-walk quiesced (fold fires
//      once, at init). Fixed by `emit::inherit_source_stale`.
// Both modes now settle at 6.
{ let a = [i64:1, i64:2, i64:3]; let s = i64:0; s <- array::fold(a, i64:0, |acc, e| acc + e); s }
